  <h2>Why Free Checkers Predict Turnitin Accurately</h2>

  <p>Turnitin, GPTZero, and Originality.ai all detect AI writing by analysing the same fundamental properties of text — specifically how predictable the word choices are (perplexity) and how much sentence length varies (burstiness).</p>

  <p>Because they target the same underlying signals, text that fools one detector almost always fools the others. This is why checking with free tools before submission is a reliable strategy.</p>

  <h2>What Free Checkers Cannot Tell You</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Plagiarism from web sources</strong> — free AI detectors do not check for copied text from websites. Use a separate plagiarism checker for this.</li>
    <li><strong>Turnitin's exact score</strong> — free tools give you a strong prediction but not the exact number Turnitin will show.</li>
    <li><strong>Whether your institution flags the score</strong> — different universities have different thresholds for action.</li>
  </ul>

